      <details>
        <summary>How do US-China trade talks affect stocks?</summary>
        <p>Trade talks introduce uncertainty. Positive developments generally lead to market rallies, while escalating tensions or tariffs often trigger sell-offs, particularly in tech and manufacturing sectors.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Which sectors are most impacted by US-China tariffs?</summary>
        <p>Semiconductors, agriculture, consumer electronics, and heavy machinery are highly sensitive due to complex global supply chains.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is decoupling in US-China relations?</summary>
        <p>Decoupling refers to the process of reducing economic interdependence between the two nations, often involving shifting supply chains and imposing export controls.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Should I sell my stocks during trade tensions?</summary>
        <p>Knee-jerk reactions are rarely advisable. Investors should focus on companies with diversified supply chains and strong domestic revenue streams to mitigate geopolitical risk.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How can I track US-China trade news?</summary>
        <p>Follow major financial news outlets, track announcements from the USTR and Commerce Department, and monitor the performance of major multinational corporations.</p>
      </details>
